doc.previous: The Royal Canberra Hospital was located on Acton Peninsula on Lake Burley Griffin; it was closed in 1991 and was demolished in 1997 in a controversial and fatal implosion to facilitate construction of the National Museum of Australia.[70][111][118][253][254] The city has 10 aged care facilities. Canberra's hospitals receive emergency cases from throughout southern New South Wales,[255] and ACT Ambulance Service is one of four operational agencies of the ACT Emergency Services Authority.[256] NETS provides a dedicated ambulance service for inter-hospital transport of sick newborns within the ACT and into surrounding New South Wales.[257]
